onal ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/UIKit\/UITextDocumentProxy","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" capabilities, like the ability to read the full document content instead of just the content closest to the input cursor."}]},{"text":"Full Document Context","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Full-Document-Context"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Apple’s native text document proxy doesn’t return all the text within the document. It instead cuts off the available text at any time, e.g. at the previous or next paragraph. This makes it hard to provide AI-based features that require more context.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit Pro therefore unlocks "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/UIKit\/UITextDocumentProxy\/fullDocumentContext(config:)"},{"type":"text","text":" proxy extensions that let you read "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"all","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" text from the proxy:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let proxy = keyboardContext.textDocumentProxy","let result = try await proxy.fullDocumentContext()"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This will provide you with all the text before and after the input cursor, as well as an aggregate of all the available text in the document."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"note","type":"aside","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The full document read operation is a best effort operation, that makes the most of the very limited capabilities that are provided by the operating system. It’s not guaranteed to return a valid result. You can configure the operation to yield better results, for instance by waiting longer when moving the input cursor, try to move more times around the edges, etc."}],"type":"